laboratory_examinations.findings: Total serum IgE level was 5000 IU/ml (normal value 0–100 IU/ml), Phadiatop and fx5E were negative.
White blood cell count of 10.34/ml with 73% of granulocytes, 5.4% of eosinophils. Immunoglobulin M level was slightly low, at 0.535 g/l (normal, 0.63–2.77 g/l).
CD3 was low at 55.1%, CD8 was low at 19.3% (normal, 20–35 g/l); CD4 and CD4/CD8 were within the normal range.
Low bone mineral density with BMD 756 mg/cm3; T-3.0, Z-1.3 indicating osteoporosis.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Markedly low bone density in relation to bone area (BMDa) has been found.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Bottled camel milk produced 8-mm induration and 30-mm erythema.
